<div class="cs-app-intro">
  <div class="cs-app-intro-icon-wrap">
    <img class="cs-app-intro-icon" src="/assets/cc/colorcard-icon.png" alt=""/>
  </div>
  <div class="cs-app-intro-text-wrap">
    <p class="cs-app-intro-text-title">Colorcard</p>
    <p class="cs-app-intro-text-subtitle">(coming soon)</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="cs-app-desc-wrap">
  <div class="cs-app-desc-border-wrap">
    <p class="cs-app-desc-title">Photo sharing game</p>
    <p class="cs-app-desc-subtitle">Share photos with friends as if they were trading cards.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="cs-app-text-wrap">
  <div class="cs-app-text-title">
    How does it work ?
  </div>
  <div class="cs-app-text-subtitle">
    <p>The idea is to replicate the behaviour of trading cards.</p>
    <p>Take a photo, add a caption and send it to friends. If they re-send it to someone, they lose it. Just like a trading card !</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="cs-techdetails-wrap mod-colorcard">
  <div class="cs-techdetails-text-wrap">
    <div class="cs-techdetails-title">Technical details (v2.0)</div>
    <div class="cs-techdetails-subtitle">
      <p>I wrote this app in Objective-C for iOS7+.</p>
      <p>It was built using the <a class="mod-mesvaccins-techdetails-link" href="http://www.objc.io/issue-13/viper.html">VIPER architecture</a> for cleanliness, testability and reusability of the code.</p>
      <p>The app consumes a JSON REST API and beta testing was done using HockeyApp.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="cs-techdetails-tags">
      <li>AFNetworking</li>
      <li>Mantle</li>
      <li>Overcoat</li>
      <li>AsyncDisplayKit</li>
      <li>Pop</li>
      <li>XCTest</li>
      <li>VIPER</li>
      <li>Autolayout</li>
      <li>GCD</li>
      <li>HockeyApp</li>
      <li>REST</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

